                <summary>Announcement of a meeting of Democrats on first day of February court to
                    find replacement for Letcher for Congress.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Hon. John Letcher and the People of the Tenth Legion.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Letcher</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Goggin</ln>
                        <fn>William L.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Article beseeches people of western Virginia to stand behind Letcher for
                    governor and mocks Whig Goggin; reminds western Virginians that Letcher had
                    politically opposed slavery in their area and wonders why they would not vote
                    for him if he shared their politics.</summary>
            </div>
